# Extinction, albedo, and scattering asymmetry for the
# Hensley & Draine (2023) astrodust+PAH Milky-Way model.
#
# Astrodust grains: random-orientation T-matrix optics
#   (Draine & Hensley 2021 dielectric, P=0.20, fFe=0, b/a=1.4);
#   Cabs, Csca and <cos> from the T-matrix Q table.
# PAH: charge-resolved DL07 absorption (neutral+cation by f_ion,
#   100 A -> 100% ionized); PAH scattering is negligible and not
#   modelled, so PAH adds to extinction via absorption only.
# Size integral over the HD23 release size distribution (per H).
# Computed from the SED pipeline optics (sed_init), all components.
# Dust mass per H, M_dust/N_H =  1.184949E-26 g/H  (rho_Ad=2.74, rho_PAH=2.0 g/cm^3; K_abs = C_abs/H / this).
